  "text": "Another effector protein of RAD51 is FBH1, a 3′-5′ DNA helicase of the UvrD family that contains an F-Box domain, a proliferating cell nuclear antigen (PCNA) -interacting protein (PIP) box, and an AlkB homologue 2 PCNA interaction motif (APIM; [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . FBH1 is recruited to sites of replication stress through interaction with PCNA [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] . In vitro, FBH1 has DNA unwinding activity and catalyzes fork regression [CITATION_5] [CITATION_6] . FBH1 can form an SKP1-CUL1-F-box (SCF) complex with E3 ubiquitin ligase activity that targets K58/64 of RAD51 [CITATION_7] [CITATION_8] and may negatively regulate RAD51 localization on chromatin . UCHL3 acts as a deubiquitinase that promotes the RAD51-BRCA2 interaction and positively regulates RAD51 chromatin localization [CITATION_9] .",
